Another High Five... PT \(\)185\(

2Q results underscore mgmt's strong execution of a concept with differentiated positioning-one with unlimited unit growth potential, a compelling payback model, and virtually no direct competition. We see momentum persisting and shares to trend back toward all-time highs over time. Reit Buy. PT to $185.

**1) Top- and Bottom-Line Blowout Expectations.** 2Q sales rose 23.7% to ~$1,027M, topping Street sets and high end of prior guidance of $995M. Comps grew +12.4% vs Street sets of +9.4%, driven by transactions (+8.7%) and ticket (+3.4%). Adj. EPS $0.81 also beat Street sets and high end of guidance of $0.50~$0.62 as FIVE's customer-focused strategy continues to deliver.

**2) Unit Growth Potential Unlimited.** FIVE opened 32 stores, ending 2Q with 1,858 units (+11.5% YoY). Mgmt continues to see ample white-space and a strong pipeline, calling out new markets being entered later this year, such as the Pacific Northwest. Mgmt also re-emphasized their selective approach to filter the pipeline to evaluate the best opportunities for store placement.

**3) Compelling Assortments and Value Proposition With Better In-Stocks.** Under Winnie's leadership, FIVE's broad-based assortment continues to resonate with consumers, with six of its eight 'worlds' delivering strong comp momentum. Improved inventory flow is driving stronger in-stocks of new, trend-right items at compelling value points, positioning the company to capitalize on consistent execution through the remainder of the year.
**4) 3Q Guide Strong...** In 3Q, mgmt expects revenue of $950M-$970M (vs cons of $929M), Comps of +5-7% (vs cons of 2.1%), and EPS of $0.12-0.24 (vs cons of $0.02).

**5) ... As FY Raised On Top-Line And Bottom-Line AGAIN.** FIVE is now guiding revenue of $4.44-$4.52B (prior $4.33-$4.42B; cons $4.42B), SSS +5-7% (+3-5%; cons 4.9%), and EPS of $4.76-$5.16 (prior $4.25-$4.72; cons $4.73). As the 3Q guide implies muted +LSD% comps in 4Q, relative to current trends top-line guidance may be conservative.
**1) Nothing...** we would coqinue buying shares here and raise our PT to $185.

**Tariff Impact.** Gives margin in Q3 is expected to have ~160bps of unmitigated tariff costs, but partially offset by fixed cost leverage. As for Q4, mgmt is expecting a ~320bps op margin decline, of which 70% is due to gross margin.

**Mitigation Strategies.** FIVE has been accelerating receipts of product which will result in elevated inventory in 3Q, while continuing to take action on vendor & manufacturing diversification. See full range of mitigation strategies here.

We like FIVE's value- oriented offering, nimble and scaling business model, ample real estate growth opportunity ahead, and the upside potential offered by Five Beyond. We believe that there is a visible path to FIVE's long- term store count target of \(3,500+\) units, which may be conservative, and that the inclusion of higher- price- point products into the company's assortment will enhance FIVE's value offering and yield a multitude of benefits that are likely underappreciated in consensus estimates. We believe \(\) 6+\(items should increase customer count, drive greater customer frequency, lift basket size, generate stronger SSS growth over the long term, and potentially enhance profitability.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Comp trends stabilize. The continued rollout of Five Beyond, which we believe could drive meaningful top- line and earnings upside in the years ahead. Modest margin headwinds driven by shrinkrelated pressures. FY27E EPS: \(\) 6.15\(Target P / E: \sim 30x;\) \mathsf{PT}: \\(185.

Comp- store sales accelerate beyond our expectations, reflecting on- trend merchandising, greater marketing success, and the further strengthening of Five Beyond. New store productivity is further aided by Five Beyond, driving even greater top- line and earnings upside. Continued scale benefits lead to better sourcing capabilities and occupancy leverage, translating to strong GM gains. Better- than- expected fixed cost leverage on higher sales. FY27E EPS: \(\) 6.75\(Target P / E: \sim 30x;\) \mathsf{PT}: \\(200.

Comps worse than expected as inflationary pressures impact spending from the lower- income consumer. Slower growth in consumer spending or a greater- than- expected consumer migration to the web. New store productivity slows as marketing fails to spread brand awareness. FY27E EPS \(\) 4.30\(Target P / E: \sim 22x;\) \mathsf{PT}: \\(95.

Top material issue(s): 1) Product Design & Lifecycle Management. Five Below is committed to exploring ways to reduce the amount of carbon it emits and energy it uses, which entails discovering new ways of packaging and offering additional responsible products. 2) Supply Chain Management. FIVE requires its vendors to meet predetermined standards as it relates to human rights and labor practices.

Company Target(s): 1) Since 2020, Five Below has sold over 35M reusable bags. 2) In 2024, FIVE reduced the amount of cardboard used by \(\sim 240\) tons, the equivalent of 4,000 trees saved. 3) Through global logistics optimization and utilization measures, Five Below shipped 192 fewer containers in 2024.

Qstomgmt: 1) What are your current priorities when it comes to your environmental initiatives? 2) Are there any cost- saving or margin effects of your environmental initiatives? 3) What are your biggest challenges when it comes to managing your vendors and upholding requirements?
Multiline and Specialty Retailers & Distributors ESG integration Refresh

The expansion of the Five Beyond permanent and seasonal offerings. A hot product trend with multiple quarters of benefit (spinners, room, tech, etc.). Growing partnerships with individuals such as Bugha and Andrea Pippins. Strong momentum in gaming and FIVE's initiatives (Local Host, Nerd Street Gamers) further benefit the business.
Source: Company data, Jefferies estimates.

Five Below, Inc.Five Below is a rapidly growing value retailer that offers a broad range of trend- right merchandise, generally priced at \(5 and below, targeted at the teen and pre- teen customer. The company operates >1,750 stores, and in FY'25 it generated sales of \~\)3.9B. Five Below was founded in 2002 and is headquartered in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.

Our \(\) 155\(price target is based on a blended target FY'27E P/E of \~27x on\) \ \(5.75\) EPS. This reflects strong unit growth and new store productivity, with potential upside from merchandising initiatives and competitor stress. Risks include product trend risk, soft SSS, and regional weather or economic pressures.
